"""![Screenshot 2026-05-21 202025.png](data:image/png;base64,)

Measure Of Shape [Skewness]

Skewness measure thr assymentry of the distribution


Skewness 0 value indicates a perfectly symmetrical distribution


Positive skewness - distribution is skewed to the Right< tail is longer on the Right>


Negative Skewness - indicates left skewed that is longer in the left

> We Use fequency and cumulative distribution

##Frequency and Cumulative Distribution

![Screenshot 2026-05-21 203620.png](data:image/png;base64,)

##Skewness

![Screenshot 2026-05-21 203853.png](data:image/png;base64,)


Negatively skewed : Mean < Median < Mode


Normal Skewed : Mean = Median = Mode


Positively Skewed : Mean > Meadian > Mode
"""

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sn

dataset.head(3)

dataset["Age"].skew()

#to check Age has Skewness or not
sn.histplot(x="Age", data=dataset)
plt.show()

dataset["Age"].mean(), dataset["Age"].median(), dataset["Age"].mode()

data = np.random.normal(0,100,100)
data

pd.DataFrame({"X":data})

